# Cloudflare headers config (Workers Static Assets reads the same
# format as Pages). One rule per block, path + indented header lines.
# Glob '*' supported.
#
# Strategy: 'no-store' on EVERY response, no exceptions. The browser
# never writes the response to disk and the bfcache is bypassed, so a
# plain reload (or even back/forward navigation) always fetches the
# live deploy. data.json is ~2.5 MB and data-blobs.json ~3.1 MB; the
# latter is lazy-loaded on first Lloc open. The trade-off vs.
# 'max-age=0, must-revalidate' is the loss of the 304 short circuit
# — every visit re-downloads the full payload — but ensures readers
# always see the latest corpus.

# Security headers — site is read-only static, no auth, no forms.
#
# CSP notes:
# - Leaflet + leaflet.markercluster are self-hosted under /vendor/.
# - style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' — index.html / app.js use inline
#   style="…" attributes and Leaflet sets inline styles on tile-layer
#   panes. Accepted: CSS-only XSS has limited impact on a read-only
#   site without auth.
# - img-src 'self' data: https://*.tile.openstreetmap.org — favicon is
#   an inline SVG data: URI; OSM tile servers serve the map raster
#   tiles consumed by the Mapa tab and Lloc mini-map.
# - connect-src 'self' — fetches are data.json + data-blobs.json.
#   Tile images are <img> resources, not fetch/XHR.
# - External Internet Archive, NGIB, Wikipedia and sibling-site links
#   are navigational (<a href>), not embedded, so don't need CSP
#   allowances.
/*
  Cache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0
  Pragma: no-cache
  Expires: 0
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: https://*.tile.openstreetmap.org; connect-src 'self'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; object-src 'none'
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), interest-cohort=()
